51.6	Adventure	Adventure	An adventure is defined as an exciting or unusual experience; it may also be a bold, usually risky undertaking, with an uncertain outcome. The term is often used to refer to activities with some potential for physical danger, such as skydiving, mountain climbing and or participating in extreme sports. The term also broadly refers to any enterprise that is potentially fraught with physical, financial or psychological risk, such as a business venture, a love affair, or other major life undertakings.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Kjelkeoverisen.jpg/260px-Kjelkeoverisen.jpg
